Don,

I believe you will find that all your front apertures are 'centered`.

If you want to modify the sight line height above bore line, you can
of course make a shorter post insert, but consider that for a low
velocity
gun, the curve of the trajectory gives you a better 'match` over a
longer
set of ranges with the higher sight line.
If you cross the sight line at say 10 Meters, your pellet may fall
back into
the line at say 15-20 meters not rising too far in the interum.-
(Numbers are a guess)
It's a lot easier to accurately hold 'under` than 'over`.

Best of luck,
MadDog

